    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the<strong> chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>peri peri spice mix </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp \u2013 these are your <strong>peri peri chips</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-battered-cod-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-chilli-mushy-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>capers</strong> finely</p><p>Cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> into quarters</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-battered-cod-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-chilli-mushy-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped capers</strong> and <strong>mayo</strong> in a small bowl with<strong> half</strong> the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong> (not sure about citrus? Try using less!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli tartare sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-battered-cod-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-chilli-mushy-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> and 30g <span class=\"text-purple\">[45g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>remaining peri peri spice mix</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add 80ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[120ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[160ml]</span> <strong>very cold water </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>batter</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-battered-cod-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-chilli-mushy-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>When the chips are almost done, pat your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and cut each fillet in half</p><p>Sprinkle both sides of the<strong> fish fillet[s]</strong> with <strong>flour</strong>, then tap off any excess</p><p>Dip the<strong> floured fish </strong>into the <strong>batter</strong> and turn it several times until fully coated</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-battered-cod-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-chilli-mushy-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> (enough to coat the base of the pan) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated fish </strong>to the pan and cook for 4-5 min on each side until cooked through, golden and crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>peri peri</strong> <strong>battered fish</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-battered-cod-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-chilli-mushy-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>blanched peas</strong>,<strong> remaining chopped chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once warm, add a large knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and mash the peas roughly</p><p>Remove the pot from the heat and stir through a squeeze of <strong>lemon</strong> <strong>juice</strong>\u2013 these are your<strong> chilli mushy peas</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-battered-cod-and-sweet-potato-chips-with-chilli-mushy-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>peri peri battered fish </strong>with the <strong>peri peri chips</strong>, <strong>chilli mushy peas</strong> and a dollop of <strong>chilli tartare sauce </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>remaining lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
